INSERT INTO `absrf_forms` VALUES (5,'Yocelin Brito Bello','ybello2','1007 S. Third St.','Champaign, IL 61820','Sophmore','3.21','app/views/static/Forms/ABSRF/ybello2/resume doc.pages',NULL,'ybello2@illinois.edu','2018 S. Washtenaw Ave.','Chicago, IL 60608','(312)714-0731','Integrative biology: broad range course across topics such as evolution and genetics\r\nMolecular and cellular biology: basic eukaryotic and prokaryotic cell processes and structures \r\nGenetics: genetic course including genomics, population and evolutionary genetics \r\nEcology: learned population, community, and ecosystem structure and function and also engaged in the scientific process \r\n','4','3','6','7','1','5','2',NULL,'Interested in a veterinary career and also animal research.\r\n','This experience will benefit me by enhancing leadership, time management, team work and communication skills. The program can enhance my knowledge in science using \"hands on\" experiences and allow me to investigate ecological research; which is beyond course level learning. It will also expose  new lab environments with new professors, allowing me to proceed with my interest in research as a career path. ','Yes, I can commit to the time requirements of the program. '),(6,'Mary Frances Donovan','mfdonov2','1202 W. Nevada','Urbana, IL 61801','Sophmore','3.43','app/views/static/Forms/ABSRF/mfdonov2/resume.docx',NULL,'mfdonov2@illinois.edu','2241 Center Ave','Northbrook, IL 60062','(847) 612-8522','I have completed MCB 150 (The Molecular and Cellular Basis of Life), IB 150 (Organismal & Evolutionary Biology), IB 204 (Genetics) and IB 299 (Introduction to Research).  This semester I am enrolled in IB 202 (Anatomy & Physiology) and IB 302 (Evolution).','3','1','5','4','2','6','7',NULL,'Although I do not have a specific career in mind, I am interested in problem solving, healthcare and biological sciences.  I would like to attend medical school, dental school or go into research.  Whatever I end up doing, keeping up with the biological research community will be important.','One of my goals is to graduate with distinction in integrative biology, in which I would have to present a long term research project in 2016.  If accepted into this program and the professor allowed me to continue working in the lab after the summer, I would have up to two years of experience and be able to implement a valuable research project.  If I am not able to continue working in the lab after the summer, this program would still be beneficial in preparing me for various career opportunities.  I would like to familiarize myself with new lab techniques, feel more comfortable in a lab setting and become passionate about a particular research project.','Yes, I have no conflicts.'),(7,'Juan Flores','jflores9','1002 COLLEGE CT','Urbana, IL 61801','Freshman','','app/views/static/Forms/ABSRF/jflores9/Juan Flores-Resume.docx',NULL,'jflores9@illinois.edu','1812 N. Keystone','Chicago, IL 60639','3098077743','I have taken IB 150 my first semester. I am currently taking IB 109 and MCB 150.','3','1','6','5','4','7','2',NULL,'At this moment my interests are to research or study animals. For that reason I would like to become a zoologist, but I would like to be in research for a while, until I have a clear picture of what my career would be.','The program will enhance my learning capabilities and it will give me hands experience. Also, the program will provide me the ability to know if research is my career choice or not.','Yes, I would not mind spending 10 weeks doing the program. I am aware of the amount of time and effort this program will entail. I feel confident there won\'t be anything to stop me from joining this program. My family will support me with my decision even if it seems to long.'),(10,'Lauren Beltran','lbeltr3','102 E. Gregory Dr. Apt. 25','champaign, Il 61820','Junior','2.85','app/views/static/Forms/ABSRF/lbeltr3/Resume.docx',NULL,'lbeltr3@illinois.edu','4312 W. Wrightwood ','Chicago, Il 60639','773-524-7592','Organismal and evolutionary biology\r\nMolecular and cellular biology - basis of life\r\nEcology\r\nGenetics\r\nAnatomy and Physiology\r\nEvolution\r\n','2','3','7','6','5','8','4','1','I am extremely interested in marine biology and all aquatic life. I hope to go to graduate school and earn a degree in marine biology and go on to start my own research. ','It would expose me to an environment where I\'m working in a team on a common project. I believe this would be a good start to my career in research. I would be learning what it is like to conduct a research question and organize a plan to test it in a non-hypothetical environment. It would also give me a chance to work with professional faculty and form connections while being in a learning environment.','Yes, I would be able to commit to all of the requirements of the 10 week program. '),(11,'Emilio Jauregui','ejaureg2','207 E. Gregory Dr., MC-540','Champaign, IL 61820','Sophmore','3.45','app/views/static/Forms/ABSRF/ejaureg2/Resume.docx',NULL,'eja1177@gmail.com','5934 N. Forest Glen Ave.','Chicago, IL 60646','7739514524','IB 150, MCB 150, IB 203, IB 204, IB 202 (currently taking), and IB 302 (currently taking)','5','1','8','7','3','4','2','6','I am currently considering a career in research.  I do not know which area of research I would like to work in but I continue to have a an open interest in many areas especially related to behavior and physiology.  I am also considering a career as a health professional, as my interest in physiology and behavior ties into the many aspects of the healthcare field.','I see this experience befitting me because it appears to be a golden opportunity to learn how research is done in the real world.  If I decide to pursue a career in research, this would be a good starting point for me.  It also seems like a great way to learn something about a certain area of biology outside of the classroom through a hands-on experience.  This is important to me because I prefer to learn something by experiencing it rather than just reading about it in a book or to have it simply told to me in the classroom.','Yes.'),(12,'Nicholas Vertin','vertin2','910 S. Third Street Room 716','Champaign, IL 61820','Sophmore','3.86','app/views/static/Forms/ABSRF/vertin2/Nick\'s Resume 2014.docx',NULL,'vertin2@illinois.edu','25059 W. Pawnee Lane','Channahon, IL 60410','8153259131','IB 150\r\nMCB 150\r\nIB 203\r\nIB 204\r\nIB 202-currently enrolled\r\nIB 302-currently enrolled\r\nIB 485-currently enrolled','8','2','7','1','4','3','5','6','After receiving a degree in Integrative Biology from the University of Illinois Champaign-Urbana, I aspire to become a physician. I plan on attending medical school, preferably in-state. I\'m not sure what type of physician to become, but I am thinking about anesthesiology. I\'m thinking about doing an MD/PhD program, but I am not sure yet.','From this experience, I would be able to expand my research background. I have already experienced research in plant biology and chemistry. By researching in animal biology, I can broaden my viewpoint and ideas on the life sciences.','Yes'),(13,'Alyssa Diane Dwyer','addwyer2','604 East Armory Avenue','Champaign IL','Freshman','3.25','app/views/static/Forms/ABSRF/addwyer2/resume2.docx',NULL,'alyssa.d.dwyer@gmail.com','3005 Providence Drive','Bloomington IL','3095302420','None','5','6','7','2','1','4','8','3','My goal is to be come a chemist, since I am a chemistry major, but I love animals and worked a zoo for quite a while, so this is mostly just exploring interests. ','Animal biology honestly would have been my second choice of major. I loved animals growing up, but at the last minute I decided I loved chemistry a bit more. I have a deep respect for the sciences, and would love to be able to explore further into this branch of science. This honestly sounds like a great internship and great learning experience, so I would love to know more about it. Also, any lab work helps with my experience in chemistry as well, so I could see this as being extremely beneficial. ','Yes, I should be able to.'),(14,'Camila Marquez','crmarqu2','904 S. Lincoln Ave','Urbana, IL 61801','Sophmore','3.21','app/views/static/Forms/ABSRF/crmarqu2/resume.pdf',NULL,'crmarqu2@illinois.edu','8043 Karlov','Skokie, IL 60076','8474144358','IB 150: participated in the merit program for this course, learned more in depth about the different biological systems, including photosynthesis, cardiovascular systems of humans and other types of animals, and evolution and natural selection. \r\nMCB 244: learned about the organization on the cellular level, tissue level, the integumentary system, bone production and system, axial and appendicular skeletal systems, the muscular tissue and system, neural tissue, and special senses\r\nMCB 246: (currently taking) learning about the different organ systems, including the digestive, brain, endocrine, blood, cardiovascular, respiratory, metabolism, immunology, renal physiology, acid/base balance, and reproductive systems\r\nIB 151: (currently taking) lab class for IB 151','5','7','4','1','6','5','2','8','My career goals are to work in the chemical industry doing research on products or in the environment and studying how certain chemicals affect the environment. I am also very interested in working in the medical field, and how certain chemicals affect biological systems or bodies. I want to go to medical school in addition to exploring the field of research. ','This experience can benefit me by helping me develop and define my skills in leadership, communication, teamwork and skills in the laboratory. I am also hoping to learn what it is like to work in the scientific discipline, and gain more experience in research. ','Yes, I can commit to the 10 week program. '),(15,'Camila Marquez','crmarqu2','904 S. Lincoln Ave','Urbana, IL 61801','Sophmore','3.21','app/views/static/Forms/ABSRF/crmarqu2/resume.pdf',NULL,'crmarqu2@illinois.edu','8043 Kar