INSERT INTO `comments` VALUES (1,'Test message for Gary from Lee','Lee Bynum, Web Master',NULL),(2,'Test message for Gary from Lee','Lee Bynum, Web Master',NULL),(3,'Test message for Gary from Lee','Lee Bynum, Web Master',NULL),(4,'Test message for Gary from Lee','Lee Bynum, Web Master',NULL),(5,'Test message from Lee to Gary','Lee Bynum, Web Master',NULL),(6,'test','sig',NULL),(7,'Test message to Gary from Lee','Lee Bynum, Web Master',NULL),(8,'Test message to Gary from Lee','Lee Bynum, Web Master',NULL),(9,'Test message to Gary from Lee','Lee Bynum, Web Master',NULL),(10,'Test message','Lee Bynum',NULL),(11,'Test message','Lee Bynum',NULL),(48,'Gary, I hope you will be well very soon, and be back with us before long.  Please take care, and I\'m sorry to learn that you need medical support at this time.','Tom Frazzetta','1'),(33,'Get well soon! ','Katy Heath\r\n','1'),(34,'Hey Gary,\r\n\r\nI\'m sorry to hear that you\'re going to be out of office due to your medical condition. I greatly appreciate all the help you have given me in terms of advice, writing a letter of recommendation, and just listening to me talk about my concerns. You\'re certainly a gifted advisor, and an incredibly great person. I hope that you heal quickly and feel better soon. Thank you so much!','Nicholas Barts','1'),(35,'Hope you feel well soon. We are all here for you. Wish you can be back soon.','','1'),(36,'Gary,\r\nI\'m sorry you are going to be out for awhile, but it\'s more important that you take care of YOU!  We hope you will be able to come by from time to time but in the meantime, the best of luck & know you are in my thoughts & prayers.\r\nMarty','Marty Forrest\r\nSIB','1'),(37,'Hi Gary,\r\n\r\nI am so sorry to hear that you are out of the office due to your medical condition. Over the last four years, you\'ve been a fantastic guide helping me to figure out just exactly what i wanted to do, and how i could literally do everything. I wish you the speediest recovery! Thank you for everything!\r\n\r\n','Geniene Minkus','1'),(38,'Hi Gary,\r\nI hope you feel better! Thank you for all the advice you gave me over the years and for encouraging me to stick to my major :) You are an incredible advisor :) Come back soon :)','Andrea Herrera\r\n','1'),(39,'Hi Gary,\r\n\r\nI really do hope you get well soon. You\'re really good at what you do and will be missed!','Best wishes from,\r\nEllen Andrews','1'),(40,'Gary,\r\nI am sorry to hear that you are out of the office due to medical leave. I just want to take time to thank you for all that you have done for not only myself but countless other students for not only providing coursework and scheduling advice but mentoring students about life through the wealth of experiences that you have shared. You are a prime example of someone who lives life to the fullest seeking the best in others for the good of all. I hope that you have a speedy recovery so that you can continue to help mentor not only the students at the University of Illinois but all of the additional high school and junior high students that you work with throughout the Champaign-Urbana area. Thank you again Gary for all you do and I will definitely keep you in my thoughts and prayers!   ','Patrick Madigan','1'),(41,'Dear Gary, \r\nGet well soon! Thank you for all your help and guidance. I really can\'t thank you enough for comforting me and giving me confidence to pursue my goals. I\'m so thankful to have met you during my time here at UIUC. ','Best Wishes,\r\nPing Lee','1'),(42,'Gary-\r\nJust a note to say that we all really appreciate everything that you do and I sincerely hope that you get better soon!! We will all miss you while you are away! ','Paige Diesner','1'),(43,'I hope to see you soon!!  ','Staci Sears','1'),(44,'Hey Gary!\r\n\r\nHope you feel better soon because I was looking forward to coming in to talk about what\'s next for me in my academic future! I love chatting about whatever comes up and I look forward to seeing you back in the office! Thank you for all you have done; you are so important for so many kids\' futures just like mine.  Can\'t wait to have you back!','Sarah Rector','1'),(45,'Gary!!!\r\nIm so sorry to hear that you are not doing well:( please continue to focus on good things and know that you are deeply loved and appreciated by all who meet you.  Youre the best, and i\'m sure the office feels somber without you. We are all praying that you feel better soon.\r\n','Caroline McCleary','1'),(46,'Healthy Wishes Gary!\r\n\r\nTake care of yourself and get well.  You will be missed while you are gone!','Lee Bynum','1'),(47,'Hey Gary,\r\nI just wanted to take some time to wish you well and hope you get well soon! I\'m sorry to hear you\'ll be out of the office because I enjoy every advisor meeting I\'ve had with you! You always give great advice and I know that your students love you. Thank you for all that you have done and will continue to do, you really are a great mentor. I\'m keeping you in my thoughts and prayers, and hope you\'ll be back soon! Best Wishes.','Megan Cleary','1'),(49,'get better soon. Remember a :-) a day makes everything much better.\r\n\r\n:-)','','1'),(50,'Get well soon!','Heather DeKlyen','1'),(51,'Get well soon Gary! You\'re a great advisor and I hope you\'ll be back soon!','Aaron Stahnke','1'),(52,'Hey Gary!\r\n\r\nI hope you recover super speedy fast! What will we all do without you? I am sending you my most positive healing thoughts! ','Chelsea Monfries','1'),(53,'Hi Gary,\r\n\r\nSo sorry to hear that you are on medical leave, but you are tenacious and I look forward to seeing your smile when you return.\r\n\r\nAll the very best,\r\n\r\nDeborah Katz-Downie','Deborah Katz-Downie','1'),(54,'Hey Gary!\r\n\r\nI\'m sorry to hear that you\'re not feeling well. Get plenty of rest and I hope you get better soon~!','Melissa Negron','1'),(55,'Hi Gary,\r\n\r\nI hope you feel better soon! You\'re a really great advisor, and have helped me a lot even in the few times we have met.','Kelsey Low','1'),(56,'Get well soon! I enjoy all of our sessions and you are very helpful!','Sarah Heeg','1'),(57,'Dear Gary,\r\n\r\nWe hope you\'re feeling better soon.','Gene and Julia Robinson','1'),(58,'Hi Gary,\r\n\r\nWishing you the best of health and a speedy recovery.  Come back soon!','Jeffrey Haas','1'),(59,'Hello, Mr. Spezia. You impacted the course of my studies forever with your kindness & willingness/ability to help. I don\'t know if you remember me, but I was a DGS student whom you helped switch into IB Honors. Please feel better soon & thank you so much for everything you\'ve done to me & every other IB student you\'ve helped counsel. ','Katy Beebe','1'),(60,'Dear Gary,\r\nYou\'ll be in our thoughts.  Best wishes for a speedy recovery.  Hang in there!','Art and Chris DeVries','1'),(61,'Gary,\r\n\r\nThanks so much for everything you\'ve helped me with over the last 4 years.  You were always available when I had a question, and you introduced me to interesting activities and clubs on campus.  If you hadn\'t helped me get credit for my study abroad classes I wouldn\'t be able to be a part time student, allowing me to save tuition for dental school.  I hope you feel better soon, and are back to work before you know it!\r\n\r\nP.S. I chose Case Western!','Valerie Sefton','1'),(62,'Hi Gary,\r\nFirst I would like to thank you for all the help you gave me. I hope you feel better and see you back soon! ????.','Maya O\'Neal','1'),(63,'Hi Gary!\r\nI wish you the best and I hope everything goes great for you. I want you to know that you\'re the best advisor I know on this campus and I refer a lot of my bio friends to you :) I hope to see you back soon again!! \r\nYour\'e awesome don\'t forget that! \r\n','Jamie Yuen ','1'),(64,'P.S Gary,\r\n\r\nClasses are going great in my Junior year here AND I have you to thank for it. You are always so calm when I come to with questions about how to make my schedule and what classes to take and you always give me great suggestions. You\'re honestly the best. ','Jamie Yuen ','1'),(65,'Hi Gary\r\n\r\nI am sorry to hear that you are not well. You are in my thoughts and \r\nI hope that you have a speedy recovery. We will miss you while you are gone.','Tracey Hickox','1'),(66,'Hi Gary --\r\n\r\nAll the best.\r\n\r\nbettina','','1'),(67,'Get well soon, Mr. Spezia! Hope to see you around campus soon!','Zach Ferguson','1'),(68,'Get well soon, Gary! You\'ve been so helpful on my journey to getting my degree.','Jen Ferchau','1'),(69,'Get well soon. You have made my four years so much easier.','Brian Zalay','1'),(70,'Hi Gary,\r\nHope you feel fine soon. We are always here for you. You do a great job for all IB student. We cannot without you. Everything will be fine. ','Yihui Zhu','1'),(71,'Hi Gary,\r\nHope you feel better soon! Thank you for all your help and support!','Madeline Curtis','1'),(72,'Gary, \r\n\r\nYou are an amazing advisor. I hope you get well soon, stay strong!','Sally Feng','1'),(73,'Hi Gary,\r\n\r\nI hope you have a speedy recovery so that we can all see you back in your office soon! You\'ve been a phenomenal advisor to so many of us in IB.\r\n\r\nGet well soon!','Chelsea Maguire','1'),(74,'Hi Gary,\r\nI hope that you have a speedy recovery! You are in our thoughts!','Andrea Chez','1'),(75,'Hi Gary,\r\n\r\nYou\'ve been a great adviser so far. I hope you get better soon!','Zach Axelrod','1'),(76,'Hi Gary!\r\nI just wanted to let you are an amazing adviser and one of the nicest people I\'ve met since coming here.\r\nI hope you get well soon!!','Leah Benuska','1'),(77,'Best adviser ever! You helped take away the stresses of signing up for classes just by being the great guy you are. Thanks so much for all your help. We all appreciate everything you have done for us, get well soon!','Haley Kinner','1'),(78,'Gary,\r\n\r\nSorry to hear about your leave, hope you feel better soon! Thank you so much for all the advice you\'ve given me, the recommendations you\'ve written, and everything you do. You\'re a great advisor! Always the best,','Matt Boyce','1'),(79,'Hi Gary,\r\n\r\nYou are in my thoughts and prayers. Thank you for helping me this past year towards graduation!','Kristina Caputo ','1'),(80,'Gary! I hope you get better soon! We need you here!\r\nYou were the most helpful advisor I have encountered on this campus. I was so stressed and you sat and took time to help me outline my semesters and find classes that I would actually enjoy! And I will be needing some more help here soon so come back ASAP :) \r\nI will keep you in my prayers','Rachael Nasralla','1'),(81,'Hey Gary! You are so helpful and friendly! Thank you for all of the times you\'ve been willing to help me at a moments notice; it always cheers me up and makes my day so much easier :) I hope you recover soon, we need you! ~~Keeping you in my prayers~~','Grace Abernathy ','1'),(82,'Gary,\r\nI hope you feel better soon and that you can come back to campus ASAP! I need ya before I graduate in August, you\'ve always been so wonderful (even when I\'m a pain crying in your office) and you\'ve helped me so much in planning out my future, I couldn\'t ask for a better advisor. The way you truly care about each one of your students really touches us. You\'ve had a major impact on my college career and I couldn\'t thank you enough! You\'ll be in my thoughts and prayers and I hope to see you soon!','Jessica Decker','1'),(83,'Gary, \r\nI am sorry to hear you aren\'t feeling well and I hope you feel better soon. You will be in my thoughts and prayers. While I never met with you for advising or anything many of my friends have and I know how much you meant to them and helped them through their time here. ','Emily','1'),(84,'Gary,\r\n\r\ni hope you feel better soon. You are a great person and advisor and it seems that so many of us are missing you already. I cant wait to see you back on campus :). Thanks again for everything. ','Lili Calderon ','1'),(85,'Dear Gary,\r\n\r\nYou are the best advisor I\'ve ever had the pleasure of meeting. Everyone I\'ve talked to in IB loves you more than you know. You\'ve definitely changed my life and I know there\'s countless others whose lives you\'ve changed for the better. I can\'t wait to talk to you again to catch up! Get better soon!','Chris Woolridge','1'),(86,'Dear Gary,\r\n\r\nThank you so much for everything you have given me, both in regards to advising me and guiding my educational career at UIUC, and for volunteering to write a letter of recommendation for me. I haven\'t forgotten my promise- I look forward to sharing with you both the schools that have accepted me and the school I ultimately decide to attend, as soon as you make a full recovery. You truly have had a profound impact in my life, and I sincerely look forward to talking with you again.','Seth LaPidus','1'),(87,'Hi Gary,\r\nGet well soon -- we\'re all pulling for you!\r\n','Stephen Downie','1'),(88,'I hope you feel better Gary! Your help has been invaluable and I hope to see you back soon so you can impact other students\' lives the way you have mine.\r\n\r\n','Corie O\'Brien','1'),(89,'Dear Gary,\r\n\r\nThank you so much for all you have done for IB and for me. I was pleasantly surprised to find someone so willing to help me succeed here at the University despite having only known me for a brief time. You are truly wonderful. Get well soon!','Caroline Ewing','1'),(90,'Hi Gary -- Just wanted to let you know how valuable your conversations with students about the Plant Bio PSM have been this semester.  As always, many thanks for putting the word out -- I\'ve enjoyed meeting some super SIB students who hold your opinions in high regard! Very best,  Joan','','1'),(91,'Congrats on your retirement and good luck in all that you do!!!','Staci','6'),(92,'Cecil,\r\nThank you so much for all your help. Great support staph mean so much to us! Even if our experiments don\'t go well we know that getting the supplies we need will be seamless.\r\nCheers','Rhiannon Peery','6'),(93,'Cecil,\r\n\r\nCongratulations on your retirement! Thank you for making me feel so welcome at SIB - enjoy this new season of life!','Caroline Ewing','6'),(94,'Dear Gary,\r\n\r\nOur thoughts are with you. Get well soon.','Surangi and Mark','1'),(95,'Congrats on retirement! Thanks for all your help over the past four years.','Surangi Punyasena','6'),(96,'Be well and enjoy the next adventure.  Thanks for being there!','Stephen Downie','6'),(97,'Cecil,\r\n    What a nice photo of you!  It reminds me of how organized your office always has been.  You have always been so professional in your dealings with me, starting with a smile and question: What can I do for you?  And, indeed, you always did prompty and efficiently what I need to have done.  How many times you made that extra trip to my office to clarify something or get a signature, etc.  I could always count on your service!\r\n    I wish you all the best in your new stage of life!\r\nCarol Augspurger','','6'),(98,'Congratulations and all the very best for your new chapter in life! \r\nBest,\r\nDeborah Katz-Downie\r\n','Deborah Katz-Downie','6'),(99,'Cecil, \r\nThanks for always being so nice and patient, despite all the weird purchase requests, last-minute orders, and PO hassles I always had for you. When I feel stressed and ready to snap at folks, I will try to remember you\'re amazing ability to stay positive. In fact, I hereby coin the phrase \"take a Cecil pill\" to remind folks (and myself) to be calm, cool, and collected!!  You will be sorely missed!!!','Melissa Chipman','6'),(100,'Hi Gary,  I hope that you get to feeling better soon!  We need you!','Becky Fuller','1'),(101,'Hi Gary.  So sorry to have you out again!  Beat it this time, too, please.','John C','1'),(102,'Cecil,\r\nThank you for all your help, patience, and double checking when the order didn\'t seem quite right. You will be very missed!\r\nI hope you enjoy your retirement. \r\nWarm wishes,\r\nKat Grennan','Aleel (Kat) Grennan','6'),(103,'Cecil,\r\n\r\nCongratulations and thanks for all your help over the many long years I\'ve known you.  Wishing you the best on the next chapter of your life.  Is Texas in there anywhere?\r\n','Debbie Black','6'),(104,'Enjoy your retirement, Cecil!','Brian Allan','6'),(105,'Get better, Gary!','Brian Allan','1'),(106,'Cecil, we will miss your smile and cheerful attitude. Have a great retirement, you deserve it!','Brett Mommer','6'),(107,'Gary, \r\nYou have been such huge help to me during my time here at U of I! Always willing to go above and beyond and genuinely interested in helping me succeed both here and in the future! Get better soon!!! \r\n\r\n ','Katie Quill','1'),(108,'Feel better soon! Thanks for all the guidance you have given me in my time here at U of I. I really appreciate it!','Brittany Kleszynski','1'),(109,'Here\'s hope for a speedy recovery! You\'ve really helped me not only figure out what I want to do with my life, but also how to get there. Thank you!','Rebecca Surroz','1'),(110,'Gary,\r\nHope you get well soon!! You will be in our prayers.','James Yoon','1'),(111,'I was wondering why I didn\'t receive a response within a couple hours of my email to you because that\'s always the norm. Most helpful advisor I\'ve ever had! Hope you get better soon.','Jake G','1'),(112,'Hey, Gary - wishing you the best and letting you know you\'re missed around the building. Sending prayers and good thoughts for your return. ','Don ','1'),(113,'Hi Cecil,\r\n\r\nIt will be very sad not to have you on campus.  Thank you for so many favors and real help in stocking my course.  You have my very best wishes for a good, happy, and deserved retirement.  Please take care always.\r\n   \r\n\r\n','Tom Frazzetta','6'),(114,'Dear Cecil,\r\n\r\nCongratulations on your retirement. I enjoyed working with you over the years and appreciate all that you did to keep my lab well stocked, and in the black.\r\n\r\nEnjoy your next chapter and I wish you the very best.','Gene Robinson','6'),(115,'Mr. King, :)\r\n\r\nI wish you all the best in your retirement!  You will be greatly missed.  I have enjoyed working with you for many, many years!  Not too many of us staff left from \"Life Sciences\".  May you enjoy your future ahead and do everything your heart enjoys.  Will miss you buddy!','Lisa Smith','6'),(116,'Cecil,\r\n\r\nDon\'t worry!  You will definitely LOVE retirement (at least for 60 days).  Then you can always sign up for extra help if you feel the need to stress yourself out again!  LOL','Carol Hall','6'),(117,'Hi Gary.  Hoping you will have a speedy recovery!  All the best.','Carol Hall','1'),(118,'Gary,\r\n\r\nYou know how much you will be missed but you won\'t get rid of seeing me that easy!  :)  Our working relationship and friendship through the past 20 years has done nothing but strengthened and enriched my life.  You are an awesome person and such an inspiration.  This is not an obstacle you cannot overcome.  Your determination and perseverance are over the top.  Do the best you can to feel better and enjoy life to the fullest.  You, as always, are in my thoughts and prayers and I will talk to and see you soon.  Take care, buddy!','Lisa \"Smitty\" Smith','1'),(119,'Cecil,\r\n\r\nCongrats on your retirement! Enjoy every second of your new found freedom! It was nice to work with you, even though it was a short stint.\r\n\r\nGood Luck','Rayme Dorsey','6'),(120,'Cecil,\r\nThank you so much for the service you\'ve given to SIB.  You have been a friendly face and patient presence when I\'ve been completely lost about how to pay a bill, order a computer, or figure out how to book and pay for the brass quintet for Convocation.  I will miss you.  I hope your retirement if filled with many breakfasts with your parents, garage sale shopping, and everything else that you love!!','Toni Helton','6'),(121,'CONGRATULATIONS Cecil on your Retirement!!!  You\'ll be missed, but it\'s now time for YOU!!','Marty Forrest','6'),(122,'Cecil, I hope you have an enjoyable retirement.  Thank you for your help tracking down orders that had gone astray and keeping us in the stuff we needed to keep this place running.','Ed Dole','6'),(123,'Cecil,\r\nCongratulations on your retirement.  I just wanted to let you know how much I have appreciated all the help with orders from obscure places you\'ve handled for me over the years and the cheerful way you got the job done; it really made my life a lot easier.  Many thanks!\r\n\r\nBest wishes for good health and lots of time to enjoy the grand kids!\r\n','RayZ','6'),(124,'Hi Cecil,\r\n\r\nCongratulations on your retirement!  I hope you enjoy every minute!  \r\n\r\nI can\'t make your party today, but I wanted to make sure I wished you a Bon Voyage!\r\n','Sarah Morris','6'),(125,'Hi Gary,\r\n\r\nI wish you a quick recovery.  Your presence is missed at SIB!\r\n\r\nThank you for all that you do,\r\n\r\nMargaret McPhillips','','1'),(126,'Hey Gary,\r\n\r\nI\'m sorry to hear that you are not well and hope that you recover quickly. I greatly value all the help you have given me over the past 3 years and really appreciate the extra effort you make in every meeting to help me find more ways to gain research and hands on experience in IB. Thank you again for writing me a letter of recommendation and I will let you know the outcome as soon as I hear back from the Shedd Aquarium. I really appreciate all that you have done for me and so many other students here. Get well soon!','Michael Kozak','1'),(127,'Gary\r\nSorry to hear you are not feeling well.  Take care of yourself.  All the best! :) ','Debbie Lanter','1'),(128,'Cecil\r\nCongratulations on your retirement!  Retirement is wonderful!  Enjoy each day and always remember to do something for yourself each day.','Debbie Lanter','6'),(129,'Hi Gary, I hope this message finds you well! i just wanted to say thank you for all the help you\'ve given me with transferring to u of i, then transferring into IB. I\'m lucky to have such a great counselor!','Kari Kosog','1'),(130,'Hey Gary,\r\nI hope you feel well soon! Thank you so much for all your help and support over the last 4 years! ','Emily Szachowicz','1'),(131,'Hope you feel better soon! Thanks for the dedication you bring to helping IB majors!','Sydney Miller','1'),(132,'Hi Gary,\r\nGet well soon! I\'m sorry to hear about your leave and I hope to see you again soon. Thanks for all the wonderful advice! Wishing you all the best!','Angela Caselli','1'),(133,'Hi Gary,\r\nSorry to hear about your leave. Thank you so much for all the support you\'ve given me during my undergraduate years. You are always so cheerful and encouraging to me. Hope you well recovery soon! We know nothing can beat your warm smiles :D','Junping Wang','1'),(134,'Hey hey Gary! \r\n\r\nI am very sorry to hear that you\'re under the weather and out of the office. Im certain many students and faculty are missing your presence. I wanted to thank you for all the time and work you dedicated to helping me get my study abroad plans off the ground and soaring! I have recently been accepted my fall program of choice: SFS Kenya & Tanzania Wildlife Management. Such quick progress would not have been possible without your help! Thanks again and best wishes for a speedy recovery.','Katie Hayward','1'),(135,'Hey Mr. Spezia,\r\n\r\nI\'m so sorry to hear that you are out of the office. You recently helped me so much when I was trying to chart out my future courses, and you are such a blessing to all of the students you help every single day. We all miss you very much, and hope that soon we can walk into the office and see you there, greeting us with your signature warm smile :D ','Ashay Vaidya','1'),(136,'I hope you get well soon Gary!','Craig','1'),(137,'Mr. Spezia,\r\n\r\nI am truly sorry that you are unwell. I just want to let you know that you really helped me a lot this year. You truly made me gain back some confidence after a tough first semester by advising me to apply for REUs this summer. I do not think I would have given myself a chance at those if it were not for your counsel. Thank you! I sincerely appreciate all you have done! Get better soon!','Paige Oboikovitz','1'),(138,'You and your family are in my prayers Mr. Spezia! You have been instrumental so far in my college career and will need your guidance in the future. Get well soon!\r\n\r\nGod Bless!','Christopher Seiboldt','1'),(139,'Hi Gary,\r\nGet well soon and I\'m sure you will! Sorry for your leave and thank you for your great advices and your effort in making IB department a wonderful place! All the best!','Tianhui Zhou','1'),(140,'Hi Gary, \r\n\r\nI wish you a quick recovery and hope you get well soon! Thank you for everything you\'ve done for SIB and myself and others. ','Mike P','1'),(141,'Gary,\r\n\r\nYou are such a special person to this university and the IB department in particular. We students owe so much more to you than we realize! Thank you for your patience and calmness with me when I come in like a whirlwind. Thank you also for going above and beyond to research programs for me when I had no idea where to even begin. Appointments with you should be longer because it always feels like catching up with an old friend and running out of time! We miss you dearly, Gary, and I\'m praying for your recovery. Thank you again for what a spectacular advisor and person you are!','Allison Canty','1'),(142,'Gary,\r\n\r\nI am sorry to hear you are on medical leave. Hope you feel well soon. Thanks for all you do to ensure success here at the University. We miss you energy and charisma!','Amanda ','1'),(143,'I hope you are feeling much better very soon! ','Shawna','1'),(144,'\r\n\r\nGet well soon and get back where you belong, giving me well-deserved grief and working hard on behalf of your students.  If I can help in any way, at any time, please do not hesitate to ask.  You are in my thoughts and prayers.  \r\n\r\n  ','Bob Steltman','1'),(145,'Hope your recovery is quick and complete.  It\'s just not the same around here without you, and all my best wishes and prayers are headed your way.  Take care, my friend.','Brad Mehrtens','1'),(146,'Hi Gary:  I hope you get well soon. You\'re one of the good ones,and I need folks like you to visit with.  My prayers are with you.  ','Joe Hinchliffe','1'),(147,'Dear Gary,\r\nI trust that you are receiving the care you need and that you are comforted and strengthen by the huge love the Illinois’ community is sending your way.  My warmest thoughts and prayers remain with you.  You are an awesome advisor for the students and for your colleagues and your influence is needed at Illinois.  I look forward to have you back!  \r\n','Mercedes Ramirez Fernandez','1'),(148,'Gary,\r\n\r\nYou certainly have my prayers for a speedy and healthy recovery.  I wish you all the best.  \r\n\"Tough times don\'t last, but tough people do\" - Robert Schuller','Chester','1'),(149,'G-Man,\r\n\r\nThinking about you and hoping that things get better for you soon. You are in our thoughts and prayers, my friend.','Clark and Barb Niepert','1'),(150,'Gary! I miss talking basketball with you. Keep cheering on the Illini while you work on your own recovery. Hang in there to quote my mother when times were tough, \"Give \'em hell\"!','Jennifer Brandyberry','1'),(151,'Gary,\r\n\r\nTake all the time you need to get better. You will be missed, but your health is far more important than any dumb ol\' job.\r\n\r\nBtw, my boys still laugh when I remind them about the wheelchair rides you gave them. They really enjoyed your visits.','Mike Faullin','1'),(152,'Get well soon, Gary . . . I wish you all the best.  ','Anna Ivy','1'),(153,'Hello, Gary!  Wishing you lots of good rest and nutrition to help in your recovery.  We look forward to having you back on campus.','Barbara H-B','1'),(154,'Hi Gary!  Sending good thoughts your way for a speedy recovery.  I hope March Madness offers a diversion to the riggers of rest and recuperation.  In the absence of Alma Mater the rest of us will welcome you with open arms upon your return to campus.  Go Illini!','Mary F. Davis, ARO / LAS','1'),(155,'Gary,\r\nSending you warmest wishes and positive thoughts for a swift recovery and return to UIUC!','Kristine McCoskey, LAS New Student Advising','1'),(156,'Hi Gary,I hope my note finds you well. If you have HBO, I recommend that you watch Game of Thrones. It\'s quite a complicated plot. I liked it so much that I\'m watching seasons 1 and 2 again. I just ordered the books.\r\nAll the very best to you my friend.','Toni Pitts','1'),(157,'All the best, Gary. You will be in my family\'s prayers.','David Unger','1'),(158,'Sending you best wishes for your health, Gary! Keeping you in our prayers.','Lauren Denofrio-Corrales','1'),(159,'Hi Gary!\r\nI wish you all the best in your recovery. May these messages show how much you are thought of and appreciated. I always enjoy a conversation with you, Gary. You are a super guy,and I will keep you in my thoughts and prayers. May you find peace and the patience you need while recovering. You will get there!! All good thoughts and prayers your way!\r\n','Rody Negangard','1'),(160,'Gary,\r\nGet well soon!  You are missed when you are away.','Scott Baker','1'),(161,'Dear Gary,\r\n\r\nFeel better soon.  I\'ll pray for you.  All my best,','Jeff Goldberg','1'),(162,'Get Well Gary!','','1'),(163,'Gary,\r\n\r\nI\'m sending good thoughts your way for a strong recovery. You\'re in my prayers. Campus isn\'t the same without you!\r\n\r\n','Bernadette So','1'),(164,'Gary,\r\n\r\nAlthough we didn\'t work together that long, I truly appreciate and value the friendship that we formed.  The office hasn\'t been the same without you.  I look forward to splitting a pot of coffee with you and buying you lunch (I owe you since you turned me on to Derald\'s fish sandwich)\r\nCheers,','Barry','1'),(165,'Son\r\nThe old family saying\"YOU NEVER KNOW WHOSE WATCHING\".\r\nThank you all.\r\n  ','DAD','1'),(166,'Hi Gary this  bit  of nonsense  comes from your old & mean really old soon to 94 come 5 August.. At this juncture in life there is little left to get excited about other than the never ending  challenge to stay ahead of father times never ending nibbling at my well being that now has me using a walker to get about.... no complaints.... I am still here go wish you well.',' Uncle Emil ','1'),(167,'','','1'),(168,'Hi Gary, there are times when we wish we could just say...\"Gone Fishing\" But You resort to the this?:-) \r\n\r\nTake care, and get well soon! You are truly missed.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Dean Davis-Smith','1'),(169,'All the best Gary!  It was good to finally meet you and although our interactions were brief, they were professional and friendly.  And for that I am very appreciative.  ','Arif Fazel','1'),(170,'Hi Gary -  I hope you are doing well and will be back soon!','Marsha Nix, ARO','1'),(171,'Gary, get well soon!  I  miss consulting with you about my IB questions. ','Jack Ikeda','1'),(172,'Gary,  Oji-Chan and Oba-Chan Kakazu Pray for your speedy recovery. Get well soon.  We love you,  Taki and Carol','','1'),(173,'What can I say about my little brother.  He is the most amazing man.  He has the biggest kindest heart.  He loves helping others whether you work with Gary or for him he always is there to help you.  He has coached many kids including my own kids in track and in there personal life.  He has been here for me as well as many other members of our family.  Anyone who knows him love him very much.  Get well soon little brother we all love you.  \r\n\r\nDarla, Jacob , Eliza Isaiah, and Kamryn','\r\nDarla Knipe','1'),(174,'Hey Gary!\r\nCarl and I wish you the best to heal fast and come back feisty!  (Boy, the lengths some people go to in order to watch basketball unimpeded. . .Ha!)  We are thinking of you!! Let us know if you need anything.','Hugs,  Carol and Carl M','1'),(175,'Hey Buddy,\r\n\r\nThanks for letting me bend your ear the other day.  I appreciate your thoughts and wisdom over the years.  Be thinking about you and wish you a speedy recovery.  Keep the faith, my friend.\r\n\r\n','Gary W.','1'),(176,'Hello Gary! I am keeping you in my thoughts and prayers and sending you positive energy your way. We can\'t wait for you to return! Best wishes for a fast recovery!','Merissa Jones','1'),(177,'Hey Gary,\r\nWhat happened to my Vermin County buddy?  Email or call me if you can!  Prayers for you!\r\n\r\n\r\n','Carol Firkins','1'),(178,'Gary,\r\n\r\nI really hope that everything is okay and you\'ll be back soon! You\'re already missed!','Brittany Bochenko','1'),(179,'Hi Gary,\r\n\r\nI wish you the best and you are definitely missed!  Take care of yourself and I hope to see you here soon!  Thanks for everything you do!','Cory Ohms','1'),(180,'Hi Gary!\r\n\r\nI hope you get well soon! Lots of people are thinking about you and sending you good thoughts.','Hannah Wright','1');
